    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-09-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="193"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                <head>193. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                    (Brzezinski) to Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d193fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Staff Material, North/South, <persName corresp="#p_PRA_1"
                            >Pastor</persName>, Country, Box 26, Jamaica, 1–9/79.
                        Confidential.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-09-22">September 22, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MMN_1">Manley</persName> Attacks on the U.S.
                        (C)</item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has read of the reaction in Jamaica to Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_MMN_1">Manley</persName>’s anti-U.S. speech before the
                    Non-Aligned Summit,<note n="2" xml:id="d193fn2">See <ref target="#d192fn2"
                            >footnote 2, Document 192</ref>.</note> including opposition leader
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEPG_1">Seaga</persName>’s statement that the populace
                    anticipates a cutoff of U.S. aid and would blame <persName corresp="#p_MMN_1"
                        >Manley</persName> for this rather than the U.S. (C)</p>
                <p>In response, the President drew an arrow to <persName corresp="#p_SEPG_1"
                        >Seaga</persName>’s comment about a cutoff of U.S. aid and wrote, “we should
                    react—why have we waited?” (C)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Zbigniew Brzezinski</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
